article.headline: Morehead State 60, SE Missouri State 55
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Shawn Williams had 17 points Thursday as Morehead State broke a 17-game losing streak against NCAA Division I teams, defeating Southeast Missouri State 60-55. The last win for the Eagles (2-15, 1-10 OVC) was Nov. 18 against Kentucky Christian, an NAIA team. After a tight first half that ended with the Eagles on top 25-24, Morehead State pushed its lead to five with 11:50 remaining. The Redhawks (6-12, 3-9) regained the lead with back-to-back 3-pointers by Roy Booker, but Morehead State came back with a rally of its own to lead 51-50 with just under 4 minutes remaining. Late free throws and a layup at the buzzer provided the final margin for the Eagles. Booker led Southeast Missouri with 22 points. Ryan Allen and Cordaryl Ballard each had 10 points for Morehead State.
